EDISON FIXTURE COMPANY, INCORPORATED PLAINTIFF-APPELLANT, v. MORRIS GREENBERG, DEFENDANT-APPELLEE. Argued October 8, 1924 Decided February 5, 1925.

Before Justices Trenchard. Minturn and Lloyd.

For the appellant, Herman B. J. Wechstein. Eor the appellee, Thomo-s P. Gurley. *198Peb Cueiam.

The evidence is not set forth in the state of the case.

The judgment for the defendant will be presumed to have beén justified by the proofs, and will be affirmed, with costs.
